  "details": "OpenEXR is a high dynamic-range (HDR) image file format originally developed by Industrial Light &amp; Magic for use in computer imaging applications.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in OpenEXR&apos;s hufDecode functionality. This flaw allows an attacker who can pass a crafted file to be processed by OpenEXR, to trigger an undefined right shift error. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to system availability.(CVE-2021-20304)",
